[id="configuring-kms-encryption"]
= Configuring Kubernetes KMS encryption
include::_attributes/common-attributes.adoc[]
:context: configuring-kms-encryption

toc::[]

Kubernetes Key Management Service (KMS) encryption provides an additional layer of security for sensitive cluster data stored in etcd by integrating with external key management systems. With KMS v2, you can use external key management providers to encrypt and decrypt data encryption keys (DEKs) used to protect etcd data.

